What Makes Top Programs Effective

The best programs focus on three types of learning simultaneously.

1. Conceptual Models

Understanding how markets work.

Example:

supply elasticity

cap rate formation

credit cycles

You already cover this in:

Unit 3 (Markets & Cycles)

2. Analytical Tools

Students must be able to evaluate deals quantitatively.

Example tools:

NOI analysis

cap rate valuation

IRR modeling

sensitivity analysis

Covered in:

Unit 11 (Investment Analysis)

3. Decision Frameworks

How professional investors make decisions.

Examples:

margin of safety

capital allocation discipline

portfolio diversification

Covered in:

Unit 16 (Institutional Capital Discipline)

